# ============================================================
# YouTube Downloader — Environment Configuration
# ============================================================
# HOW TO USE:
#   cp .env.example .env.local
#   Edit .env.local with your values (never commit .env.local)
# ============================================================


# ------------------------------------------------------------
# YT_DLP_PATH  (optional)
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Absolute path to the yt-dlp executable.
# Default: "yt-dlp" — assumes yt-dlp is available in your PATH.
#
# You only need to set this if:
#   - yt-dlp is NOT in your PATH, or
#   - you want to pin a specific version/location
#
# Install yt-dlp (one-time setup per machine):
#   macOS:         brew install yt-dlp
#   Ubuntu/Linux:  sudo apt install yt-dlp  OR  pip install yt-dlp
#   Windows:       winget install yt-dlp
#                  (or download from https://github.com/yt-dlp/yt-dlp/releases)
#
# Examples:
#   macOS (Homebrew Intel):  /usr/local/bin/yt-dlp
#   macOS (Homebrew Apple Silicon / M1-M4):  /opt/homebrew/bin/yt-dlp
#   Linux:                   /usr/bin/yt-dlp
#   Windows:                 C:\Users\YourName\AppData\Local\Microsoft\WinGet\Links\yt-dlp.exe
#
# YT_DLP_PATH=yt-dlp


# ------------------------------------------------------------
# FFMPEG_PATH  (optional — almost never needed)
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# Absolute path to the ffmpeg binary.
# Default: the bundled binary from @ffmpeg-installer/ffmpeg, which is
# automatically resolved for your OS (macOS x64/arm64, Windows, Linux).
# You do NOT need to install ffmpeg manually.
#
# You only need to set this if:
#   - you want to use YOUR OWN system ffmpeg instead of the bundled one
#
# Examples:
#   macOS (Homebrew Intel):          /usr/local/bin/ffmpeg
#   macOS (Homebrew Apple Silicon):  /opt/homebrew/bin/ffmpeg
#   Linux:                           /usr/bin/ffmpeg
#   Windows:                         C:\ffmpeg\bin\ffmpeg.exe
#
# FFMPEG_PATH=
